<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="403" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d403">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1112/86: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-30T17:00:00-05:00">December
                                    30, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>162. Your 520, December 17, 4 p.m. We are considering suggesting the same
                            person for membership on the Economic and Raw Materials Committees. As
                            apparently the Raw Materials Committee is to be composed largely of
                            members of the Economic Committee we presume that meetings of the two
                            bodies will be coordinated. However, we desire any information you may
                            be able promptly to secure concerning such coordination and concerning
                            the probable frequency, dates and duration of meetings of the Raw
                            Materials Committee.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>